{"action": "edit", "code": "def find_teal_block(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array, returns a list of tuples representing the indices of all the teal blocks in the array.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    List[Tuple[int, int]]: A list of tuples representing the indices of all the teal blocks in the array.\n    \"\"\"\n    teal_list = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == teal:\n                teal_list.append((i, j))\n    return teal_list\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    teal_list = find_teal_block(input_grid)\n    for item in teal_list:\n        input_grid = color_between_teal_and_red(input_grid, item)\n        input_grid = change_teal_to_yellow(input_grid, item)\n        input_grid = color_black_to_teal_symmetrical_row(input_grid, item)\n    return input_grid\ndef change_teal_to_yellow(input_grid: np.ndarray, teal_block: Tuple[int, int]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array and the indices of a teal block, changes the color of the block to yellow.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    teal_block (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple representing the indices of the teal block.\n    \n    Returns:\n    np.ndarray: A 2D numpy array with the color of the teal block changed to yellow.\n    \"\"\"\n    input_grid[teal_block[0]][teal_block[1]] = yellow\n    return input_grid\ndef color_black_to_teal_symmetrical_row(input_grid: np.ndarray, teal_block: Tuple[int, int]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array and the indices of a teal block, finds two red bars with the same length from the grid. \n    Then finds the position of the teal block relative to the top red bar and the corresponding number of rows in the other red bar. \n    Finally, colors the black block in the corresponding row of the bottom red bar to teal.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    teal_block (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple representing the indices of the teal block.\n    \n    Returns:\n    np.ndarray: A 2D numpy array with the black block in the corresponding row of the bottom red bar colored to teal.\n    \"\"\"\n    row = teal_block[0]\n    col = teal_block[1]\n    top_red = None\n    bottom_red = None\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        if top_red is None and np.all(input_grid[i] == red):\n            top_red = i\n        elif top_red is not None and np.all(input_grid[i] == red):\n            bottom_red = i\n            break\n    if bottom_red is None:\n        bottom_red = input_grid.shape[0] - 1\n    top_red_length = bottom_red - top_red + 1\n    if row <= top_red_length:\n        corresponding_row = row\n    else:\n        corresponding_row = bottom_red - row\n    for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n        if input_grid[bottom_red][j] == black:\n            corresponding_col = j\n            break\n    input_grid[bottom_red - corresponding_row][corresponding_col] = teal\n    return input_grid\n# you get a input grid and a point.\n# First you should get row of the point and find a red block in the same row.\n# Then you should color all block between teal and red to teal.\ndef color_between_teal_and_red(input_grid: np.ndarray, teal_block: Tuple[int, int]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array and the indices of a teal block, colors all blocks between teal and red blocks in the same row to teal.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    teal_block (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple representing the indices of the teal block.\n    \n    Returns:\n    np.ndarray: A 2D numpy array with all blocks between teal and red blocks in the same row colored to teal.\n    \"\"\"\n  