nally, colors the black block in the corresponding row of the bottom red bar to teal.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    teal_block (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple representing the indices of the teal block.\n    \n    Returns:\n    np.ndarray: A 2D numpy array with the black block in the corresponding row of the bottom red bar colored to teal.\n    \"\"\"\n    row = teal_block[0]\n    col = teal_block[1]\n    top_red = None\n    bottom_red = None\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        if top_red is None and np.all(input_grid[i] == red):\n            top_red = i\n        elif top_red is not None and np.all(input_grid[i] == red):\n            bottom_red = i\n            break\n    if bottom_red is None:\n        bottom_red = input_grid.shape[0] - 1\n    top_red_length = np.sum(input_grid[top_red] == red)\n    bottom_red_length = np.sum(input_grid[bottom_red] == red)\n    if top_red_length != bottom_red_length:\n        return input_grid\n    if row < top_red:\n        return input_grid\n    elif row > bottom_red:\n        return input_grid\n    else:\n        corresponding_row = bottom_red - (row - top_red)\n        input_grid[corresponding_row][np.where(input_grid[corresponding_row] == black)[0][col]] = teal\n        return input_grid\n# you get a input grid and a point.\n# First you should get row of the point and find a red block in the same row.\n# Then you should color all block between teal and red to teal.\ndef color_between_teal_and_red(input_grid: np.ndarray, teal_block: Tuple[int, int]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a 2D numpy array and the indices of a teal block, colors all blocks between teal and red blocks in the same row to teal.\n    \n    Parameters:\n    input_grid (np.ndarray): A 2D numpy array representing the input grid.\n    teal_block (Tuple[int, int]): A tuple representing the indices of the teal block.\n    \n    Returns:\n    np.ndarray: A 2D numpy array with